text
@d128 26
a153 6
However there is a fair amount of third party software one might want
to use in addition to the base system.
Typically, users would use pre-compiled binary packages to add such
functionality.
But in order to create these binary packages in the first place,
OpenBSD uses the ports tree.
d156 3
a158 2
In this handbook, we will explain how the ports tree works, when you
should use it and how to maintain it.
